

This causes a decrease in the risk of cancer as the proto-oncogene HRas is repressed by attracted kinase proteins via transcriptional repressive histone modification H2ASerMSK1.





This sequence increases the expression of beta-amyloid by increasing the affinity of the promoter using histone modifications that encourage acetylation.





The H2ALys4Esa1 histone modification causes a increase in gene expression. This can cause for an increase in cancer risk as the chance of a cell becoming cancerous increases when these modifications are applied to a proto-oncogene.
